{
  "local_port": 41126,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I am planning a 4 day Holiday in North India. Where can I go?",
  "response": "Here\u2019s a well-organized 4-day holiday plan for North India, offering diverse options based on your interests:\n\n---\n\n### **Option 1: Classic Golden Triangle (Delhi, Agra, Jaipur)**  \n**Day 1: Delhi**  \n- **Explore:** Red Fort, Jama Masjid, Chandni Chowk, India Gate, Humayun\u2019s Tomb, Qutub Minar.  \n- **Stay:** Delhi (Connaught Place or Aerocity for convenience).  \n\n**Day 2: Delhi \u2192 Agra (3\u20134 hours drive)**  \n- **Explore:** Taj Mahal (sunrise visit), Agra Fort, Mehtab Bagh, and local markets for marble handicrafts.  \n- **Stay:** Agra.  \n\n**Day 3: Agra \u2192 Jaipur (4\u20135 hours drive, stop at Fatehpur Sikri)**  \n- **Explore:** Abandoned Mughal city Fatehpur Sikri en route. In Jaipur, visit Amber Fort, Hawa Mahal, and City Palace.  \n- **Stay:** Jaipur (heritage hotels recommended).  \n\n**Day 4: Jaipur \u2192 Delhi (5 hours drive)**  \n- **Morning:** Jantar Mantar, Albert Hall Museum, or shop for textiles/jewelry.  \n- **Return:** Head back to Delhi by evening.  \n\n---\n\n### **Option 2: Spiritual & Adventure (Rishikesh & Haridwar)**  \n**Day 1: Delhi \u2192 Rishikesh (6\u20137 hours drive/flight to Dehradun + 1-hour drive)**  \n- **Explore:** Evening Ganga Aarti at Triveni Ghat.  \n- **Stay:** Rishikesh (riverside resorts or ashrams).  \n\n**Day 2: Rishikesh**  \n- **Activities:** River rafting, visit Beatles Ashram, suspension bridges (Laxman Jhula), and temples.  \n- **Optional:** Yoga/meditation sessions.  \n\n**Day 3: Rishikesh \u2192 Haridwar (1-hour drive)**  \n- **Explore:** Har Ki Pauri Ghat, Mansa Devi Temple, and local markets.  \n- **Evening:** Attend Ganga Aarti.  \n\n**Day 4: Haridwar \u2192 Delhi (4\u20135 hours drive)**  \n- **Morning:** Visit Chilla Wildlife Sanctuary or relax by the Ganges.  \n\n---\n\n### **Option 3: Hill Escape (Shimla)**  \n**Day 1: Delhi \u2192 Shimla (8\u20139 hours drive/2-hour flight to Chandigarh + 3-hour drive)**  \n- **Explore:** Mall Road, The Ridge, and Jakhu Temple.  \n- **Stay:** Shimla (colonial-era hotels).  \n\n**Day 2: Shimla**  \n- **Explore:** Viceregal Lodge, Christ Church, and Scandal Point.  \n- **Optional Toy Train Ride:** Kalka-Shimla UNESCO Heritage route.  \n\n**Day 3: Day Trip to Kufri/Mashobra**  \n- **Activities:** Horseback riding, hiking, or visit Himalayan Nature Park.  \n\n**Day 4: Shimla \u2192 Delhi**  \n- **Return:** Drive/flight back to Delhi.  \n\n---\n\n### **Option 4: Cultural Deep Dive (Amritsar)**  \n**Day 1: Delhi \u2192 Amritsar (6-hour train/1.5-hour flight)**  \n- **Evening:** Golden Temple night ceremony.  \n- **Stay:** Amritsar.  \n\n**Day 2: Amritsar**  \n- **Explore:** Golden Temple, Jallianwala Bagh, Partition Museum.  \n- **Evening:** Wagah Border flag-lowering ceremony.  \n\n**Day 3: Food & History**  \n- **Food Tour:** Try Amritsari kulcha, lassi, and street food at Lawrence Road.  \n- **Optional:** Visit Ram Tirath Temple or Durgiana Temple.  \n\n**Day 4: Return to Delhi**  \n\n---\n\n### **Tips:**  \n- **Transport:** Hire a private car for flexibility or use trains (book in advance via IRCTC).  \n- **Entry Tickets:** Pre-book Taj Mahal (https://asi.payumoney.com) and Amber Fort.  \n- **Weather:** Winters (Oct\u2013Mar) are ideal for all options; summers (Apr\u2013Jun) suit hill stations.  \n\nChoose based on your preference for history, spirituality, nature, or culture! \ud83c\udf04\ud83d\udd4c\ud83c\udfd4\ufe0f",
